	<h2>Loop-the-loop ride with friction</h2>

	<p>A box of mass m is fired using a spring (with a spring constant k) that is initially compressed to a 
	distance x<sub>0</sub> beyond its relaxed length. The box encounters a rough surface of length L and a 
	coefficient of kinetic friction \(\mu\)<sub>k</sub>, the surface of the track is otherwise frictionless. 
	The box  then goes up a loop of radius R. What should x<sub>0</sub> be if the box is to fall off the loop 
	at point P? Give your answer in the quantities given: k, L, \(\theta\), R, \(\mu\)<sub>k</sub>.</p>
